The paper deals with a natural language processing task of extreme summarization, which involves creating a one-sentence summary of a news article. This task falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and involves machine learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for identifying pertinent content in a document.
